				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Actually, it doesn't HAVE to be kindly with the Clerics of Underfoot. The reason you might think so is because it has to be very high amiable. When I turned in the four fairy dusts for the first time, my faction was amiable, and it didn't work. So I went and turned in another bag of bone chips. My faction was still amiable, but when I gave Priestess Ghalea the fairy dusts it worked. So if you want to be safe, it is a good idea to get it up to kindly, but it doesn't have to be.
				</font>
